{
  "_comment": "Copy this file to local.settings.json and fill in real values for local development. local.settings.json is gitignored. In production, these values are set as Azure App Settings — none of them are secrets and none require Key Vault.",
  "IsEncrypted": false,
  "Values": {
    "AzureWebJobsStorage": "UseDevelopmentStorage=true",
    "FUNCTIONS_WORKER_RUNTIME": "node",
    "FUNCTIONS_EXTENSION_VERSION": "~4",

    "_comment_tenants": "Multi-tenant configuration. JSON array (single-line string in the env var). Each entry maps a public slug used in the embed snippet (data-tenant=\"...\") to a Microsoft Bookings business, a service ID under that business, and the origins permitted to embed it. The widget code never sees businessId or serviceId; site owners never type either. The OPTIONAL requiredStaffEmails field gates slot eligibility — only slots where at least ONE listed email is free will appear (OR semantics, case-insensitive). If omitted or empty, defaults to 'any staff available'. To add a new property, add an entry and restart the Functions app.",
    "BOOKING_TENANTS": "[{\"slug\":\"example-property\",\"businessId\":\"BookingsBusiness@example.com\",\"serviceId\":\"00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000\",\"label\":\"Example Property\",\"allowedOrigins\":[\"https://example.com\",\"http://localhost:8080\"],\"requiredStaffEmails\":[\"sales@example.com\"]}]",

    "_comment_local_auth": "For LOCAL development only: when running outside Azure, the Functions runtime cannot use Managed Identity. Provide an Azure service principal via the AZURE_TENANT_ID, AZURE_CLIENT_ID, and AZURE_CLIENT_SECRET environment variables, or sign in via 'az login' and DefaultAzureCredential will pick up your developer credentials. None of these are needed in production — the deployed Functions App uses its system-assigned Managed Identity automatically.",
    "AZURE_TENANT_ID": "00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000"
  },
  "Host": {
    "LocalHttpPort": 7071,
    "CORS": "*",
    "CORSCredentials": false
  }
}
